Film buffs have the chance to own a piece of Hollywood cult history as the luxury home featured in Ferris Bueller's Day Off is up for sale.

The 5,300 square foot house in Highland Park, Chicago, Illinois, is on sale priced at $1.5million.

It featured in the iconic 1986 film, starring Matthew Broderick as Ferris, as the home of Bueller's neurotic best friend Cameron Frye.

