The home, part-suspended over a wooded ravine, comprises a main four-bedroom house and a separate pavilion with its own kitchen and bathroom.

The pavilion also has room for four cars.

In a classic scene, Frye has a breakdown in the room after returning his father's beloved Ferrari but discovering that hundreds of miles have been added to its speedometer.

He then kicks the car repeatedly before sending it crashing through the glass walls into the ravine below.

The home is on the market for the second time in two years after the owners failed to sell at $1.65million in 2011.

